race.comment: WITH STRENGTH (6) made very light work of his rivals when resuming here over the 900m last time. Will appreciate the drop in the weights and is drawn well again, with McDougall taking over. Sure to be right there at the business end. DIVAZOU (8) capitalised on his bright start to the prep when leading pillar-to-post here over this journey two weeks ago. Full fitness now and can repeat the dose. TOOMPINE (2) is a handy gelding returning for the Thompson camp. Looked sharp in his jump-out win but has to lug the big weight, which could prove the difference. GETTY (5) is hard to trust, though his best is good enough for a race like this. Should be able to lead from an inside gate and that'll go a long way to him returning to his best form.
